      'So why does a cigarette seem to "help"? That is where the trap is. You light up exactly when the wave is already on its way down — and the brain draws a false conclusion: "that is what saved me." But if you had not smoked, the wave would have fallen just the same. Only without a new dose of nicotine, without feeding the dependence, without the rebound tomorrow.',
