      'Then take a few long, slow exhales. Not inhales — exhales: they switch the nervous system into a calm mode. And just watch the wave grow and fade, like a surfer who does not fight the wave but glides over it. This technique is called urge surfing. You are not suppressing the urge and not obeying it. You are riding it out.',
