      'If you are on day two or three without cigarettes and feel like you are losing your mind — stop for a second. You are not losing your mind. You are exactly on schedule. What you feel right now is felt by almost everyone, and there is a precise explanation for it.',
      'Nicotine clears the brain receptors in about 72 hours. All that time the brain, used to a dose every hour, keeps demanding its share in confusion. That is why on days 2–4 withdrawal symptoms peak: irritability over trifles, anxiety with no cause, broken sleep, strong cravings, a general "off" feeling.',
